# Part 4 — Security, Autoscaling, Chaos Engineering & Production Readiness

---

## 12. Security & Encryption Model

### 12.1 Authentication Chain

```
Client ──WSS──▶ Envoy (TLS 1.3 termination)
                    │
                    ▼
              WS Handshake
              ┌─────────────────────────────────┐
              │ Authorization: Bearer <JWT>     │
              │ X-Device-Id: <device-uuid>      │
              │ X-Client-Version: <semver>       │
              └─────────────────────────────────┘
                    │
                    ▼
              Gateway Pod: JWT Verification
              ┌─────────────────────────────────┐
              │ 1. Verify signature (RS256)     │
              │ 2. Check exp, iat, nbf          │
              │ 3. Verify tokenVersion vs DB    │
              │ 4. Check user status ≠ SUSPENDED│
              │ 5. Extract userId, role         │
              │ 6. Rate limit check             │
              └─────────────────────────────────┘
                    │ FAIL → close(4401, 'Unauthorized')
                    │ PASS ↓
              Connection Established
```

### 12.2 Per-Call Authorization

```typescript
async function authorizeCall(callerId: string, targetId: string): Promise<AuthResult> {
  // Parallel checks for speed
  const [blockStatus, privacySettings, followStatus, callSpamScore] = await Promise.all([
    checkBidirectionalBlock(callerId, targetId),
    getUserPrivacy(targetId),
    getFollowStatus(callerId, targetId),
    getCallSpamScore(callerId),
  ]);

  if (blockStatus.blocked) return { allowed: false, reason: 'BLOCKED' };
  if (callSpamScore > 50) return { allowed: false, reason: 'SPAM_DETECTED' };

  // Privacy-based call permissions
  switch (privacySettings.callPermission) {
    case 'EVERYONE': return { allowed: true };
    case 'FOLLOWERS': return { allowed: followStatus.isFollowing, reason: 'NOT_FOLLOWING' };
    case 'MUTUAL': return { allowed: followStatus.isMutual, reason: 'NOT_MUTUAL' };
    case 'NOBODY': return { allowed: false, reason: 'CALLS_DISABLED' };
  }
}
```

### 12.3 Replay Attack Prevention

```typescript
// Each signaling message includes a nonce + timestamp
interface SignalEnvelope {
  nonce: string;       // crypto.randomUUID()
  timestamp: number;   // Date.now()
  payload: SignalEvent;
  signature: string;   // HMAC-SHA256(nonce + timestamp + payload, sessionSecret)
}

async function validateSignalEnvelope(envelope: SignalEnvelope): Promise<boolean> {
  // 1. Check timestamp is within 30s window
  if (Math.abs(Date.now() - envelope.timestamp) > 30_000) return false;

  // 2. Check nonce hasn't been used (Redis SET with NX + 60s TTL)
  const isNew = await redis.set(`nonce:${envelope.nonce}`, '1', 'EX', 60, 'NX');
  if (!isNew) return false; // Replay detected

  // 3. Verify HMAC signature
  return verifyHmac(envelope);
}
```

### 12.4 Media Encryption

| Layer | Protocol | Key Exchange | Notes |
|-------|----------|-------------|-------|
| Signaling transport | TLS 1.3 (WSS) | ECDHE | All signaling encrypted in transit |
| DTLS handshake | DTLS 1.2+ | ECDHE | WebRTC mandatory; authenticates media channel |
| Media encryption | SRTP (AES-128-CM) | Derived from DTLS | All audio/video encrypted |
| TURN relay | DTLS over TURN | Same as P2P | TURN server cannot decrypt media |
| ICE candidates | Encrypted in signaling | Via WSS channel | No plaintext candidate exposure |

