## 14. Chaos Engineering & Disaster Recovery

### 14.1 Chaos Experiments

| Experiment | Tool | Frequency | Expected Outcome |
|-----------|------|-----------|------------------|
| Kill random WS pod | Chaos Monkey | Hourly (staging) | Users reconnect <5s, zero dropped calls |
| Redis shard failure | Litmus | Weekly | Sentinel failover <15s, presence rebuilt |
| Region network partition | AWS FIS | Monthly | Cross-region calls degrade; same-region unaffected |
| TURN cluster overload | Custom load gen | Weekly | Auto-spill to adjacent region |
| DNS failover | Route 53 failover test | Monthly | Traffic shifts <60s |
| Mass disconnect (50K) | Custom | Monthly | Staggered reconnect, no thundering herd |
| Kafka broker kill | Litmus | Weekly | ISR shrinks, auto-replacement, no data loss |

### 14.2 Thundering Herd Prevention

```typescript
function calculateReconnectDelay(attempt: number, baseMs: number = 1000): number {
  // Exponential backoff with full jitter
  const exponentialDelay = Math.min(baseMs * Math.pow(2, attempt), 30_000);
  return Math.random() * exponentialDelay;
}

// Client-side reconnect logic
async function reconnectWithBackoff() {
  let attempt = 0;
  while (attempt < MAX_RECONNECT_ATTEMPTS) {
    const delay = calculateReconnectDelay(attempt);
    await sleep(delay);
    try {
      await connectWebSocket();
      return; // Success
    } catch {
      attempt++;
    }
  }
  // All attempts failed — show "connection lost" UI
}
```

### 14.3 Disaster Recovery — RPO/RTO

| Component | RPO | RTO | Strategy |
|-----------|-----|-----|----------|
| Active calls | 0 (in-flight) | 10s (reconnect) | Client ICE restart |
| Presence data | 0 | 5s | Rebuilt on reconnect |
| Call history | <5s | <60s | Kafka → PG async replication |
| User data | 0 | <30s | CockroachDB multi-region |
| TURN allocations | N/A | Immediate | New allocation on reconnect |

