|--------|--------|----------------|----------|
| `ws_active_connections` | Gateway custom metric | >18K per pod | P2 |
| `call_setup_latency_p99` | OpenTelemetry | >500ms | P1 |
| `call_setup_latency_p50` | OpenTelemetry | >120ms | P2 |
| `call_failure_rate` | Derived | >2% over 5 min | P1 |
| `turn_allocation_failure_rate` | coturn metrics | >5% over 5 min | P1 |
| `turn_active_allocations` | coturn metrics | >900 per node | P2 |
| `redis_connected_clients` | Redis INFO | >8000 per shard | P2 |
| `redis_memory_usage_pct` | Redis INFO | >80% | P1 |
| `kafka_consumer_lag` | Kafka metrics | >10K messages | P2 |
| `ice_negotiation_failure_rate` | Client telemetry | >10% over 5 min | P1 |
| `presence_sync_latency_p99` | Custom | >500ms | P3 |
| `pod_restart_rate` | Kubernetes | >3 restarts in 5 min | P2 |

### 15.2 Distributed Tracing

```typescript
// OpenTelemetry instrumentation for call lifecycle
import { trace, SpanKind } from '@opentelemetry/api';

const tracer = trace.getTracer('call-signaling');

async function initiateCall(callerId: string, input: CallInput) {
  return tracer.startActiveSpan('call.initiate', {
    kind: SpanKind.SERVER,
    attributes: {
      'call.caller_id': callerId,
      'call.target_id': input.targetUserId,
      'call.type': input.callType,
      'call.region': LOCAL_REGION,
    },
  }, async (span) => {
    try {
      const callId = generateCallId();
      span.setAttribute('call.id', callId);

      // Authorization sub-span
      const authResult = await tracer.startActiveSpan('call.authorize', async (authSpan) => {
        const result = await authorizeCall(callerId, input.targetUserId);
        authSpan.setAttribute('call.auth.allowed', result.allowed);
        authSpan.end();
        return result;
      });

      // Presence lookup sub-span
      const location = await tracer.startActiveSpan('call.presence_lookup', async (presSpan) => {
        const loc = await resolveUserLocation(input.targetUserId);
        presSpan.setAttribute('call.target.region', loc?.region || 'offline');
        presSpan.end();
        return loc;
      });

      span.setStatus({ code: 0 }); // OK
      return { callId, status: 'SIGNALING' };
    } catch (error) {
      span.setStatus({ code: 2, message: (error as Error).message });
      throw error;
    } finally {
      span.end();
    }
  });
}
```

### 15.3 Call Quality Telemetry Pipeline

```
Client (every 5s during call)
    │
    │  { callId, timestamp, 
    │    audio: { jitter, packetLoss, roundTripTime, codec },
    │    video: { frameRate, resolution, bandwidth, codec },
    │    ice:   { candidateType, localType, remoteType },
    │    network: { connectionType, effectiveType } }
    │
    ▼
WS Gateway ──▶ Kafka (topic: call.quality.telemetry)
                    │
                    ▼
              ClickHouse (columnar storage)
                    │
                    ├──▶ Grafana Dashboards (real-time QoS)
                    ├──▶ Anomaly Detection (statistical, Flink)
                    └──▶ Monthly QoS Reports
```

